==English==
===Etymology===
French ''hectare'', from Greek [[hect-]] + French [[are]]

===Noun===
'''hectare'''

#A unit of surface area (''symbol'' [[ha]]) equal to 100 [[are]]s (that is, 10,000 [[square metre]]s, or approximately 2.5 [[acre]]s), used for measuring the areas of geographical features such as land and bodies of water.

